    <description>Purpose: Table of maximum MAF values vs. system voltage. The output of the air meter is clamped to lower values as system voltage drops off. Used to compare with engine speed max MAF, KtTPSD_dm_MaxMAF_VsRPM, to check if the MAF could possibly be limited. Format: 1x9; 16-bit big-endian unsigned integer; Y = X * 0.0078125; units unitless. Source: KtTPSD_dm_MaxMAF_VsVoltage at 0x078AD6 in winols_astra.csv. Astra mapping/local notes: HP Tuners Airflow Correlation P0068 Max Airflow vs. IGNV. WinOLS/Damos symbol KtTPSD_dm_MaxMAF_VsVoltage, maximum MAF vs. system/ignition voltage used to check voltage-based MAF limiting. Source 0x078AD6 -&gt; target 0x07A586. 1x9 unsigned 16-bit big-endian, scaled X / 128.</description>
