    <title>TurboOverspeedMaxPressureRatio_04D9BC</title>
    <description>Purpose: Maximum compressor pressure ratio to avoid turbo overspeed or surge. A table in function of corrected massflow. Cal hint: Derived from the speed lines or surge line in the compressor map and adjusted in altitude test when observing measured turbo speed. Axes: X - Flow axis for the compressor map. Expressed in corrected massflow. Cal hint: Derived from the compressor map from the supplier. Format: 1x8; 32-bit big-endian IEEE-754 float; Y = X; units unitless. Source: KaBSTC_r_CompPressRatioMaxSpd at 0x047984 in winols_astra.csv. Astra mapping/local notes: Likely HP Tuners [ECM] 33491 Turbo Overspeed Max Pressure Ratio equivalent. BSTC KaBSTC_r_CompPressRatioMaxSpd family, 1x8 32-bit big-endian float pressure-ratio row with corrected mass airflow axis at 0x04DC44. Target axis matches the HPT screenshot; this Astra original row decodes as 3.00, 2.85, 2.675, 2.475, 2.275, 1.975, 1.575, 1.00, so the middle cells are higher than the provided HPT screenshot values.</description>
